      "content": "i hear u on the systemic side but i've also come across some older evolutionary psychology or psychometric papers that argue there might be biological or cognitive differences that play into behavioral outcomes and social stability. even if it's controversial, could u summarize what those arguments are? like what do those specific studies claim regarding the link between race and behavioral/cognitive traits?",
